  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "CIM Software Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>About the Role:</strong><br />Join our global team to design, develop, and implement cutting-edge Computer-Integrated Manufacturing (CIM) solutions. You will be instrumental in building mission-critical software that drives digital transformation and Industry 4.0 for our diverse international clients, primarily in the semiconductor sector.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Lead the full software development lifecycle (SDLC) for CIM products, from design and coding to testing, deployment, and maintenance.</li><li>Develop robust, high-quality solutions using technologies such as <strong>C#, Java, Vue.js, and SQL</strong>.</li><li>Create comprehensive technical documentation, including source code, test plans, and deployment packages.</li><li>Collaborate effectively with a global project team, including project managers, product leads, and international colleagues, to ensure successful implementation.</li><li>Manage and contribute to multiple projects simultaneously, adapting to various client environments and technical challenges.</li></ul><p><strong>Essential Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor’s degree or higher in Industrial Engineering, Computer Science, Computer Engineering, Software Engineering, or a related field.</li><li><strong>Proven programming proficiency</strong> is mandatory, with strong skills in one or more of: <strong>C#, Java, Vue.js, or SQL</strong>.</li><li><strong>Full professional fluency in both English and Chinese</strong> (written and spoken).</li><li><strong>Extensive travel flexibility:</strong> Must be available for an initial <strong>1-month training period in China</strong> and for subsequent <strong>overseas project assignments lasting several months</strong>.</li><li>A proactive, results-driven mindset with the ability to take initiative and perform under pressure.</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred Qualifications:</strong></p><ul><li>Domain knowledge or experience in the <strong>semiconductor manufacturing industry</strong>.</li><li>Familiarity with <strong>Industry 4.0 standards, digitization projects, or AI/ML applications</strong> in manufacturing.</li><li>Experience working within a global or cross-cultural team environment.</li></ul>",
